            path: 'references/secret-patterns.md',
            role: 'reference',
            content:
                '# Secret Patterns\n\nA detection catalogue used by `scripts/scan-secrets.sh` and by manual review. Patterns are written\nin `grep -E` / Perl-Compatible Regular Expression (PCRE) style. **These are detection patterns, not\nstorage** — never paste a real secret into a report. Always redact.\n\n**Golden rules**\n- **Run locally only. Never exfiltrate.** The scanner must not make network calls; it reads files\n  on disk and prints redacted results to the terminal.\n- **Always redact in output.** Show only the first 4 and last 4 characters; mask the middle with\n  `*`. Example: `AKIA****************MPLE`. Short matches (≤ 8 chars) should be fully masked.\n- **Mark likely placeholders.** Values containing `example`, `sample`, `dummy`, `CHANGEME`,\n  `changeme`, `your-`, `xxxx`, `placeholder`, `<...>`, `TODO`, or found in `.env.example` /\n  `*sample*` files are probably not real and should be flagged `likely_placeholder: true`.\n- **Confirm before alarm.** A regex match is a *lead*, not proof. Verify the surrounding context.\n\n---\n\n## Pattern catalogue\n\n| Name | Pattern (`grep -E`) | Notes |\n|---|---|---|\n| AWS access key id | `AKIA[0-9A-Z]{16}` | Also `ASIA` (temporary), `AGPA`, `AIDA`, `AROA` prefixes for other id types |\n| AWS secret access key | `(?i)aws.{0,20}?(secret|access).{0,20}?[\'\\"][0-9a-zA-Z/+]{40}[\'\\"]` | 40-char base64-ish; high false-positive without the `aws` context anchor |\n| Private key block | `-----BEGIN ([A-Z]+ )?PRIVATE KEY-----` | RSA/EC/OPENSSH/PGP private keys; always real if present |\n| JSON Web Token (JWT) | `eyJ[A-Za-z0-9_-]{10,}\\.[A-Za-z0-9_-]{10,}\\.[A-Za-z0-9_-]{10,}` | Three base64url segments; may be a non-secret signed token, still review |\n| Slack token | `xox[baprs]-[0-9A-Za-z-]{10,}` | bot/app/user/refresh/legacy tokens |\n| Slack webhook | `https://hooks\\.slack\\.com/services/T[0-9A-Z]+/B[0-9A-Z]+/[0-9A-Za-z]+` | Incoming webhook URL |\n| GitHub personal token (classic) | `ghp_[0-9A-Za-z]{36}` | Repo/admin scope possible |\n| GitHub OAuth token | `gho_[0-9A-Za-z]{36}` | |\n| GitHub server/refresh tokens | `gh[su]_[0-9A-Za-z]{36}` | `ghs_` (server-to-server), `ghr_` (refresh) |\n| GitHub fine-grained token | `github_pat_[0-9A-Za-z_]{22,}` | Newer fine-grained PAT format |\n| Google API key | `AIza[0-9A-Za-z_-]{35}` | Maps/Firebase/etc. |\n| Google OAuth client id | `[0-9]+-[0-9A-Za-z_]{32}\\.apps\\.googleusercontent\\.com` | Often public, but flag |\n| Stripe secret key | `sk_live_[0-9A-Za-z]{16,}` | Live secret key — high severity |\n| Stripe publishable key | `pk_live_[0-9A-Za-z]{16,}` | Publishable; lower severity but still flag |\n| Stripe restricted key | `rk_live_[0-9A-Za-z]{16,}` | |\n| Twilio account SID | `AC[0-9a-fA-F]{32}` | Pair with auth token |\n| SendGrid key | `SG\\.[0-9A-Za-z_-]{22}\\.[0-9A-Za-z_-]{43}` | |\n| NPM token | `npm_[0-9A-Za-z]{36}` | |\n| Generic password assignment | `(?i)(password\\|passwd\\|pwd)\\s*[:=]\\s*[\'\\"][^\'\\"]{6,}[\'\\"]` | Filter placeholders |\n| Generic secret assignment | `(?i)(secret\\|secret[_-]?key)\\s*[:=]\\s*[\'\\"][^\'\\"]{8,}[\'\\"]` | |\n| Generic token assignment | `(?i)(token\\|auth[_-]?token\\|access[_-]?token)\\s*[:=]\\s*[\'\\"][^\'\\"]{8,}[\'\\"]` | |\n| Generic API key assignment | `(?i)(api[_-]?key\\|apikey)\\s*[:=]\\s*[\'\\"][^\'\\"]{8,}[\'\\"]` | |\n| PostgreSQL connection string | `postgres(ql)?://[^:@/\\s]+:[^@/\\s]+@[^/\\s]+` | Embedded `user:pass@host` |\n| MySQL connection string | `mysql://[^:@/\\s]+:[^@/\\s]+@[^/\\s]+` | |\n| MongoDB connection string | `mongodb(\\+srv)?://[^:@/\\s]+:[^@/\\s]+@[^/\\s]+` | |\n| Redis connection string | `redis://[^:@/\\s]*:[^@/\\s]+@[^/\\s]+` | |\n| AMQP connection string | `amqps?://[^:@/\\s]+:[^@/\\s]+@[^/\\s]+` | |\n| Basic auth in URL | `https?://[^:@/\\s]+:[^@/\\s]+@[^/\\s]+` | Any `scheme://user:pass@host` |\n| Azure storage key | `(?i)AccountKey=[0-9A-Za-z+/=]{40,}` | In connection strings |\n| Private SSH key reference | `(?i)ssh-(rsa\\|ed25519\\|dss)\\s+[0-9A-Za-z+/=]{100,}` | Public keys are not secret; private ones above are |\n| High-entropy hex | `\\b[0-9a-fA-F]{40,}\\b` | Last resort; very noisy — only with key-like context |\n\n---\n\n## Redaction guidance\n\nFor a matched value `V`:\n- If `length(V) <= 8`: replace entirely with `*` of equal length.\n- Else: keep `V[0..3]`, append `*` × `(length-8)` (cap the run of stars for readability, e.g. max\n  24), keep `V[length-4..length]`.\n- Never print the full line verbatim — print `file:line  <type>  <redacted-snippet>`.\n\nExample redactions:\n```\nAKIAIOSFODNN7EXAMPLE      -> AKIA************MPLE\nghp_a1b2c3d4e5f6g7h8...   -> ghp_********************h8j9\nsk_live_51HxAbCdEf...     -> sk_l****************dEf2\n```\n\n## False-positive notes\n- `.env.example`, `*.sample`, `*.template`, fixtures, and test files frequently contain fake\n  secrets — scan them, but mark hits as `likely_placeholder`.\n- Common placeholder sentinels: `CHANGEME`, `change-me`, `example`, `dummy`, `placeholder`,\n  `your-api-key-here`, `xxxxxxxx`, `<your-token>`, `${...}`, `{{...}}` (templating), `***`.\n- Public keys, OAuth *client ids*, and publishable keys are lower severity than secret/private\n  material — still report, but rank below live secrets and private keys.\n- A JWT in a test fixture or a documentation example is usually not a live credential.\n',
