                '<!--\n  Configuration Scan report template.\n  Fill in every section. Replace bracketed [...] placeholders. Delete rows that do not apply.\n  Status legend:\n    OK      = meets best practice\n    concern = works but risky, or a missing-but-important setting\n    fail    = insecure or clearly wrong (must fix)\n  Discipline: never list a finding without the File and a concrete Recommendation (the fix + why).\n  Keep output org-agnostic. Secrets must already be redacted before they reach this report.\n  End the report with the literal line: CONFIG_SCAN_COMPLETE\n-->\n\n# Configuration Scan Report\n\n**Scope:** [repository / path scanned]\n**Date:** [YYYY-MM-DD]\n**Mode:** Read-only (no files modified)\n\n## 1. Inventory of configuration found (by area)\n\n<!-- Summarize what find-config.sh discovered. List representative files; collapse large groups. -->\n\n- **Infrastructure as Code (IaC):** [count] — [e.g. Terraform under infra/, CloudFormation template.yaml]\n- **Continuous Integration / Continuous Delivery (CI/CD):** [count] — [e.g. .github/workflows/*.yml]\n- **Containers:** [count] — [e.g. Dockerfile, docker-compose.yml]\n- **Kubernetes / Helm:** [count] — [e.g. k8s/deployment.yaml, charts/app/values.yaml]\n- **Runtime config:** [count] — [e.g. application.yml, .env.example]\n- **Linters run:** [e.g. tflint (ran), hadolint (ran), yamllint (missing), shellcheck (ran)]\n- **Secret scan:** [count] findings ([n] likely placeholders) — all values redacted\n\n## 2. Findings\n\n| Area | Check | Status | File | Recommendation |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n| Secrets | [check] | [OK/concern/fail] | [path:line] | [recommended value + why] |\n| CI/CD | [check] | [OK/concern/fail] | [path:line] | [recommended value + why] |\n| Containers | [check] | [OK/concern/fail] | [path:line] | [recommended value + why] |\n| Scaling/runtime | [check] | [OK/concern/fail] | [path:line] | [recommended value + why] |\n| IaC | [check] | [OK/concern/fail] | [path:line] | [recommended value + why] |\n\n<!-- Add one row per check assessed. Reference the actual file/line read. -->\n\n## 3. Top fixes (ranked)\n\n<!-- Rank by severity x likelihood. Each item: what, where, the fix, why it matters. -->\n\n1. **[fail]** [title] — [file:line]. Fix: [recommended change]. Why: [risk if unfixed].\n2. **[fail]** [title] — [file:line]. Fix: [...]. Why: [...].\n3. **[concern]** [title] — [file:line]. Fix: [...]. Why: [...].\n4. **[concern]** [title] — [file:line]. Fix: [...]. Why: [...].\n5. **[concern]** [title] — [file:line]. Fix: [...]. Why: [...].\n\n## 4. Cost notes\n\n<!-- Use references/cost-drivers.md. State driver, where it appears, cheaper alternative. -->\n\n- **[driver]** — [file/resource]. Cheaper alternative: [...]. Est. impact: [high/medium/low].\n- **[driver]** — [file/resource]. Cheaper alternative: [...]. Est. impact: [high/medium/low].\n\n## 5. Notes / boundaries\n\n<!-- Note anything deferred: code-level security -> security-audit; AWS-specific depth -> aws-expert.\n     Note assumptions (e.g. ".env.example is not runtime config; real values injected via [where]"). -->\n\n- [deferred / assumption / where real secrets are injected]\n\nCONFIG_SCAN_COMPLETE\n',
